        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #bed230;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">Generating a PDF&#160;output using a multilingual target uses the same process as PDF&#160;stitching<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive,Snippets.Snippet1"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Output/PDF_Output/Stitching_PDFs.htm">Stitching PDFs</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. However, creating a multilingual target automates the process and allows you to work from multiple Flare projects at once. Additionally, because you do not need to generate each PDF&#160;separately every time the document is updated, generating output from a multilingual PDF&#160;target saves considerable time. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive,Snippets.Snippet2">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Language_Support/Selecting_a_Language.htm#HowToSelectLanguagesTarget">How to Select Languages for a Specific Target</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
